      <guid>//localhost:1313/posts/jellyfin/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h4 id=&#34;castgarden-video&#34;&gt;CastGarden Video&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;iframe title=&#34;Jellyfin, It&#39;s all you need!&#34; width=&#34;100%&#34; height=&#34;450&#34; src=&#34;https://cast.garden/videos/embed/2e59016f-712a-4d3f-bf6d-c1e6eea547a9&#34; frameborder=&#34;0&#34; allowfullscreen=&#34;&#34; sandbox=&#34;allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-popups&#34;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;click-here-to-watch-this-video-on-torhttpcastgardn7yj746n7nyt3udot5orhpqfs36sl7rq2y3yd4su6ruuddydonionw6hwsjutewx7xusgtxj8tj2&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://castgardn7yj746n7nyt3udot5orhpqfs36sl7rq2y3yd4su6ruuddyd.onion/w/6HWSJuTEWX7xusGtxj8tJ2&#34;&gt;Click here to watch this video on Tor&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Originally published December 2023&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&#xA;Jellyfin is an open source streaming media server. It can be hosted on a VPS or in your local network on an old laptop or even a Raspberry Pi. The specs required to run it are pretty low so it can run on just about anything.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
